{"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/0210AuthFlowChange","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"sections":[],"abstract":[{"text":"Learn about how to set up your project with the new authentication flow changes.","type":"text"}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/atprotokit\/0210authflowchange"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"overview","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"With the release of 0.26.0 comes a new migration flow for ATProtoKit developers. This change is fairly small, but this article will still cover what to expect in order to clear any confusion."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Authentication Flow","anchor":"Authentication-Flow","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Previously, when you wanted to authenticate to an AT Protocol service, you used an initializer from "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration","type":"reference"},{"text":", which contained the ","type":"text"},{"code":"handle","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"password"},{"type":"text","text":" parameters. Then, you would use ATProtocolConfiguration.authenticate(authenticationFactorToken:) and passed the instance to the "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtoKit","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"class"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"code":["let config = ATProtocolConfiguration(handle: example.bsky.social, password: hunter2)","","Task {","    do {","        \/\/ You can put it in here…","        try await config.authenticate()","","        let atProto = ATProtoKit(sessionConfiguration: config)","","        \/\/ Or here…","        try await config.authenticate()","    } catch {","        throw error","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"With version 0.26, this has been changed slightly:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["let config = ATProtocolConfiguration()","","Task {","    do {","","        let atProto = ATProtoKit(sessionConfiguration: config)","","        \/\/ Enter the handle and password in here.","        try await config.authenticate(","            handle: example.bsky.social,","            password: hunter2","        )","    } catch {","        throw error","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Here are the changes being made:"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"’s initializer no longer takes the "},{"code":"handle","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"password"},{"text":" parameters: now, ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/authenticate(with:password:)","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" is responsible.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This is the only external change. However, more has been made internally:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/UserSession"},{"text":" is no longer stored inside of ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration"},{"text":": now, a new ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"actor"},{"type":"text","text":" named "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/UserSessionRegistry","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" holds all instances of the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"struct"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A ","type":"text"},{"code":"UUID","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" value has been added to the "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"class","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". This value is linked to all objects that are related to the session. This is part of the new initializer for ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":", named "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/init(pdsURL:keychainProtocol:configuration:canResolve:)"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration","isActive":true},{"text":" now closely follows ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SessionConfiguration"},{"text":". In fact, the following methods are no longer stored in the ","type":"text"},{"code":"class","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", but have moved to default implementations of the ","type":"text"},{"code":"protocol","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/authenticate(with:password:)"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/getSession()","type":"reference"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/refreshSession()","isActive":true}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/deleteSession()","type":"reference","isActive":true}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A new "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"protocol"},{"text":", named ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SecureKeychainProtocol","isActive":true},{"text":", will now manage the management of the password, access token, and refresh token. An ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"actor"},{"text":", named ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/AppleSecureKeychain","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" is available for applications running on Apple’s platforms."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"anchor":"SessionConfiguration","level":2,"text":"`SessionConfiguration`","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"As mentioned previously, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SessionConfiguration"},{"type":"text","text":" now has default configurations for each of the required methods. It is also "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Sendable"},{"text":" and requires a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"class"},{"text":" to conform to it. The default implementation assumes you’re using an App Password to authenticate by default, but you’re able to create new implementations for your own conforming ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"class"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Furthermore, the "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SessionConfiguration\/authenticate(with:password:)-272a8","type":"reference"},{"text":" method handles Two-Factor Authentication, but the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"protocol"},{"type":"text","text":" can also handle OAuth. This is thanks to a "},{"code":"AsyncStream","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"-related properties, named ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SessionConfiguration\/codeContinuation","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SessionConfiguration\/codeStream","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"text":"Auto-managing the Keychain","type":"heading","anchor":"Auto-managing-the-Keychain","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"As mentioned earlier, a new ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"protocol"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"code":"actor","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" have been made: "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SecureKeychainProtocol"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/AppleSecureKeychain","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" respectively. This manages the keychain items for the password and refresh token, as well as storing the access token in-memory.","type":"text"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The access token is being stored in-memory due to how frequently the token expires."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"style":"note","name":"Note","type":"aside"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/AppleSecureKeychain"},{"type":"text","text":" conforms to "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SecureKeychainProtocol","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" and is the default object used for Apple platforms. It’s also the default object used when initializing with "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration","isActive":true},{"text":". However, you’re free to create your own implementation if it doesn’t suit your needs.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"aside","style":"note","name":"Note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"At this time, Linux and Windows developers will need to implement their own ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"actor"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"class"},{"type":"text","text":" to achieve the same effect. However, default "},{"code":"actor","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"s for those platforms will be created at a later date."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]}],"kind":"article","metadata":{"title":"0.21 to 0.26 Authentication Flow Migration","role":"article","modules":[{"name":"ATProtoKit"}],"roleHeading":"Article"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit"]]},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"references":{"doc://ATProtoKit/documentation/ATProtoKit/UserSessionRegistry":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/UserSessionRegistry","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/atprotokit\/usersessionregistry","abstract":[{"text":"A registry that manages ","type":"text"},{"code":"UserSession","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" instances, keyed by "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"UUID"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"UserSessionRegistry"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"UserSessionRegistry","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","title":"UserSessionRegistry"},"doc://ATProtoKit/documentation/ATProtoKit/ATProtocolConfiguration/getSession()":{"abstract":[],"kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/atprotokit\/atprotocolconfiguration\/getsession()","type":"topic","title":"getSession()","role":"